          .section-content(ng-if="selectedSection == 'build'")
            h2.content-text.spacer Open Source Programmer Tools
            p There have been several occassions when I find myself working in a repetitive manner or doing something that I find complex more than once. I decided some time ago to begin creating tools that would help me (first and foremost) and eventually any other programmer, make building things easier and faster. The kinds of tools I've been creating so far have been short code snippets that perform a single operation, CSS libraries and ORMs.
            h2.content-text Utilities
            p Another of my major interests is developing utility applications (for web, desktop or mobile) that could eventually turn into profitable businesses. I've worked on quite a few, though not finished with any yet, and I'm interested in collaborating on any of these ideas.
            p My major areas of focus here include education, services, advertising and expert systems.

          .section-content(ng-if="selectedSection == 'design'")
            h2.content-text Content Loading...
            p I've spent most of the past few years doing mostly coding and hence haven't had time to build my design portfolio. I do have a couple of things I've worked on but there has been little time to put them together. Be sure to check back for an update.
    section#contact-section
      .container
        .row
          .col-md-8.col-md-offset-2
            h2 Get in touch      
            p Get in touch with me to discuss interesting ideas around Software Development, Mobile Application Development, Open Source any other thing worth the while.        
            form#contact-form(novalidate name="contact" ng-submit="sendMessage()")
              .form-group.has-feedback(ng-class="{'has-error': contact.iName.$dirty && contact.iName.$error.required, 'has-success': contact.iName.$valid}")
                label(for='name-field') Name               
                input#name-field.form-control(type='text' placeholder='Enter name' required ng-model='inquiry.name' name="iName")
                span.glyphicon.glyphicon-ok.form-control-feedback(aria-hidden="true" ng-if="contact.iName.$valid")
                span#nameSuccessStatus.sr-only(ng-if="contact.iName.$valid") (success)
                span.glyphicon.glyphicon-remove.form-control-feedback(aria-hidden="true" ng-if="contact.iName.$dirty && contact.iName.$error.required")
                span#nameErrorStatus.sr-only(ng-if="contact.iName.$dirty && contact.iName.$error.required") (error)
              .form-group.has-feedback(ng-class="{'has-error': contact.iEmail.$dirty && (contact.iEmail.$error.required || contact.iEmail.$error.email), 'has-success': contact.iEmail.$valid}")
                label(for='email-field') E-mail Address
                input#email-field.form-control(type='email' placeholder='Enter email' required ng-model='inquiry.email' name="iEmail")
                span.glyphicon.glyphicon-ok.form-control-feedback(aria-hidden="true" ng-if="contact.iEmail.$valid")
                span#emailSuccessStatus.sr-only(ng-if="contact.iEmail.$valid") (success)
                span.glyphicon.glyphicon-remove.form-control-feedback(aria-hidden="true" ng-if="contact.iEmail.$dirty && (contact.iEmail.$error.required || contact.iEmail.$error.email)")
                span#emailErrorStatus.sr-only(ng-if="contact.iEmail.$dirty && contact.iEmail.$error.required") (error)
              .form-group
                label(for='phone-field') Phone Number
                input#phone-field.form-control(type='phone' placeholder='Enter Phone Number' ng-model='inquiry.phone' name="iPhone")           
              .form-group(ng-class="{'has-error': contact.iMessage.$dirty && contact.iMessage.$error.required, 'has-success': contact.iMessage.$valid}")
                label(for='message-field') Message
                textarea#message-field.form-control(placeholder='Enter message' ng-model='inquiry.message' name="iMessage" required)
              button.btn.btn-default(type='submit', ng-click='sendMail' ng-disabled="!contact.$valid") Send Message  
